<TEXT>
jury selection in the second bensonhurst racial 
slaying trial ended thursday but the defense attorney argued the 
panel couldnt be impartial because of widespread pretrial 
publicity 
the jurors four of whom are black will decide the fate of john 
vento 21 who backed out of a deal with prosecutors to trade 
testimony for immunity 
in march vento was charged with murder riot assault unlawful 
imprisonment and other crimes in the slaying of yusuf hawkins 16 
hawkins who was black was fatally shot in august after he and 
three black friends were chased through predominantly white 
bensonhurst by a mob of batwielding whites 
the four black teens were unarmed and had gone into the brooklyn 
neighborhood to look at a used car for sale 
joseph fama 19 convicted last month in hawkins death was 
sentenced on monday to the maximum 32 and twothirds years to life 
in prison 
keith mondello also 19 was acquitted of murder and 
manslaughter but was convicted of riot unlawful imprisonment and 
discrimination he received the maximum 5 13 years to 16 years in 
prison 
judge thaddeus owens rejected a request by ventos attorney 
gerald dichiara to postpone the trial and scheduled opening 
arguments to begin monday 
dichiara requested that ventos trial be put off for at least 
two months arguing that the national attention the murder and 
trial has attracted made it impossible to find an impartial jury 
i still believe that the timing of this jury selection is 
improper and i do believe the jurors are under a strain to be fair 
and impartial dichiara said 
after the shooting vento reportedly told detectives he saw fama 
shoot hawkins he testified before a grand jury investigating the 
case and was granted immunity from prosecution in exchange for 
agreeing to take the witness stand against his friends 
but he backed out of the deal and fled the city around christmas 
in march after forcing a onemonth delay in the start of famas 
and mondellos trial vento surrendered to the fbi in dayton ohio 
he is being held without bail 
</TEXT>
