<TEXT>
swiss authorities have imposed an 
immediate ban on imports of british cattle and beef as a precaution 
against mad cow disease 
a government statement thursday said the measure was designed to 
prevent products banned from european community markets being sold 
to switzerland which is not a member of the 12nation trading bloc 
the swiss ban includes all live cattle beef on the bone and 
cattle feed made from animal byproducts 
mad cow disease or bovine spongiform encephalopathy a 
degenerative nervous disorder has killed 13000 cows in britain 
over the past four years there is no proof that humans are at risk 
from eating contaminated beef 
france germany and italy last week lifted bans on british beef 
imports as part of an ec compromise a meeting of ec farm ministers 
agreed to limit british exports of live cattle to calves under six 
months of age and to introduce a certification system showing that 
beef exports were from herds where no traces of the disease were 
found in the past two years 
</TEXT>
