<TEXT>
basic cable television rates climbed at twice 
the rate of inflation last year according to a report that 
refueled the drive in congress to reregulate subscriber charges 
the prices for the lowestcost basic service and most popular 
cable services in 1989 increased an average of 10 percent from 
1450 to 1595 the congressional general accounting office said 
the total average cable bill went up 5 percent from 25 to 2636 
the inflation rate was 4 percent to 5 percent rate for the year 
said gao the investigative arm of congress 
gao reported last year that basic cable rates increased 29 
percent from december 1986 to october 1988 
rep edward j markey dmass who requested the gao survey 
said the results showed that congress must consider legislation 
that will rein in the renegade operators in the cable industry 
he said the report should erase any lingering doubts on the 
need to move forward with legislation that enhances competition 
and ensures reasonable rates 
