<TEXT>
the manufacturer of mazola corn oil announced that 
it would drop claims that imply the product reduces cholesterol 
cpc international inc based in englewood cliffs nj said 
thursday it had signed agreements with the federal trade commission 
and attorneys general in 10 states 
in a statement cpc said its future advertisements would avoid 
the use of statements which might be misinterpreted to mean that 
the use of corn oil would by itself lower serum cholesterol 
massachusetts attorney general james shannon said he and his 
colleagues challenged ads that made claims such as mazola does 
what they said it could turn back my cholesterol i didnt believe 
it until my level dropped 17 percent 
the states alleged that the advertisements stressed the 
cholesterol lowering properties of these products without placing 
proper emphasis on the importance of the total diet 
todays consumers want to eat right and they are often swayed 
by the claims made by food producers shannon said but any 
food touted as a magic cure without stressing the need for an 
allaround healthy diet does consumers more harm than good 
cpc said the ads in question already had been withdrawn for 
other reasons months ago the company said it continues to believe 
that the interpretation of the advertising by the states and ftc 
does not reflect consumer understanding of this advertising 
the company also said it has supplied numerous studies 
supporting its position that a lowfat lowcholesterol diet which 
