<TEXT>
trillions of hungry microbes ate their 
way through an oil slick friday as officials counted on an 
experimental method to help with the cleanup from the wrecked 
norwegian tanker mega borg 
this is breakthrough technology texas land commissioner 
garry mauro said of the process called bioremediation 
rolling in open seas aboard a 41foot coast guard boat 
officials sprayed a square acre in the gulf of mexico that was 
intermittently laced and blanketed by oil 
bioremediation uses naturally occurring bacteria that have been 
bred as supereaters to break down oil into harmless fatty acids 
that later are eaten by marine life said carl oppenheimer who 
developed the process 
oppenheimer a university of texas microbiologist who has been 
working on the process for 15 years predicted success within one 
or two days there will be a clear square acre in the middle of the 
slick he said 
i think it is going to open the door now to bioremediation on 
a much wider scale he said 
skeptics have criticized oppenheimers work mauro said because 
the concept is so simple 
oppenheimer would only say of the experiment its been a long 
time coming 
he said some tests have been performed on controlled spills in 
inner harbor areas but never on the open sea 
bioremediation was applied last month for the exxon valdez spill 
in alaska microbes were used to clean some rocks on the shore of 
the prince william sound officials here allowed a test on the 
slick from the norwegian supertanker that exploded june 8 
we need bioremediation said texas water commission chairman 
bj buck wynne iii this is a man who had an idea and no one 
would listen he hasnt been able to get through all the snake oil 
salesmen 
oppenheimer said crews would return later to retrieve samples of 
the water that was treated with the microbes he said there would 
approximately 53 billion microbes per square centimeter 
about 100 pounds of the sandlike substance was mixed with sea 
water and sprayed onto the slick 
oppenheimer said the slick about three miles southeast of the 
mega borg probably was about oneeighth of an inch thick markers 
were set to track the movement of the area that was treated 
he said he believed the process could remove about 90 percent of 
the oil compared with the 5 or 10 percent he said skimmers could 
remove oppenheimer described skimmers as mostly cosmetic 
