the 3000member south lebanon army helps patrol the security 
zone that israel declared in south lebanon in 1985 to guard against 
crossborder guerrilla raids 
police said no casualties were reported in the mortar machine 
gun and rocketpropelled grenade exchanges between christian troops 
loyal to rebel gen michel aoun and militiamen of samir geageas 
lebanese forces 
the interchristian battles in east beirut and christian 
communities to the north eased off thursday morning but tension 
remained high in the enclave 
at least 1036 people have been killed there and 2774 wounded 
since the fighting broke out jan 30 it has been some of the worst 
interchristian fighting in lebanons 15year civil war which has 
more often pitted christians against moslems 
a truce in the interchristian showdown was declared may 17 but 
violations have been frequent 
