<TEXT>
consumers who are worried about the ozone or 
overcrowded landfills will soon be able to look for a new 
environmental seal of approval when deciding what to buy in the 
supermarket 
an independent nonprofit organization called green seal will 
test products for their cradletograve impact on the 
environment and award seals a bold green check arched over a blue 
globe to those that meet its standards 
were trying to harness the most powerful forces we have 
available in the united states the forces of the marketplace to 
try to achieve environmental goals denis hayes chairman of 
earth day 1990 and chairman and chief executive officer of green 
seal said thursday 
at a news conference at the new york academy of sciences he 
said green seal will start early next year by awarding seals in 
five product categories light bulbs laundry cleaners house 
paint toilet paper and facial tissue 
these products were selected because they are used in almost 
every household in the country and some are clearly friendlier to 
the environment than others said norman dean the programs 
executive director 
hayes said green seal will not issue seals for food 
in april the american heart association yanked its seal of 
approval program for foods low in sodium cholesterol and saturated 
fats after the federal food and drug administration said it would 
not support the program 
the fda said what goes on food labels is a government 
responsibility 
green seal inc was founded last year by rena m shulsky a 
partner in a manhattan real estate firm and president of a 
bostonbased media consulting firm she said she came up with the 
idea while standing in a grocery store aisle wondering which 
laundry detergent would be friendlier to the environment 
i thought why doesnt someone put a seal on these things a 
little seal of approval would help me get out of the supermarket a 
lot quicker 
green seals first task will be to determine the standards by 
which the products will be judged said dean in doing so it will 
examine the full life cycle of each product category from raw 
material to when the consumer recycles it or throws it into the 
garbage 
the organization intends to solicit advice from manufacturers of 
the products public interest organizations trade associations and 
government officials in establishing its criteria for awarding 
seals 
once the standards are set companies at their own cost may 
submit their products for testing by independent laboratories 
selected by green seal 
products that get the green seal check of approval will be 
licensed to use the seal logo in their advertising for a threeyear 
period the licensing fees will be structured on a sliding scale to 
prevent hardship for smaller companies 
according to a poll conducted by research amp forecasts inc for 
green seal 79 percent of those surveyed said they would be more 
likely to purchase a product with the green seal if choosing 
between two products of the same price and equal quality 
green seal is not the first sealofapproval program for 
environmentally preferable products west germany has had a program 
for 10 years canada for three years and japan for a couple of 
years hayes said 
also green cross certification co based in oakland calif 
launched an environmental certification program for products in 
april with three west coast grocery chains and one in phoenix 
three food chains in the northeast and canada will join the 
program in july said stan rhodes president of green cross 
