met with white house chief of staff john sununu on may 7 and said 
he promised them bush would veto the bill if sent to his desk 
presidential spokesmen later repeated the veto threat 
senate passage came after leaders worked out a bipartisan 
agreement to take up the bill quickly and avoid a roll call vote 
