involved bundles of debt 
in the late 1980s about half of all funds raised by 
nonfinancial companies were borrowed compare that with the two 
previous decades when threequarters of all money raised by 
americas companies was in the form of equity 
there are many big differences between debt and equity and one 
of them is that holders of corporate equity dont threaten when 
theres a recession they might sell their shares but many will 
hold steady until the skies brighten 
those who lend money do not have that same commitment they want 
their loans repaid and they dont want to hear about the bad 
weather or poor sales or the companys need to spend on machinery 
no excuses please just pay the bill with interest 
