<TEXT>
the new york stock exchanges decision to phase 
in 24hour securities trading during the 1990s comes amid 
intensifying worldwide competition that is eroding the big boards 
market share 
regional stock exchanges foreign markets and independent 
electronic services offering cheaper trading are offering investors 
alternatives for trading nyse stocks 
meanwhile other exchanges and private services are offering 
offhours trading in the rush to capitalize on new technology that 
lets investors trade securities almost whenever and wherever they 
want 
anyplace else where you can trade securities represents 
competition john w bachman managing partner of the st louis 
brokerage edward d jones amp co said friday 
if the new york stock exchange is determined to remain what 
many people believe is the strongest market in the world they 
cant ignore it he said 
nyse chairman john j phelan jr on thursday unveiled a 
fivestep plan to trade securities after the exchanges traditional 
daytime hours the plan would culminate in 24hour trading by the 
end of the decade 
roundtheclock trading already is reality in the foreign 
currency and us treasury bond markets where dealers conduct 
transactions via telephone and computer links the two chicago 
futures markets plan to begin computerized extendedhours trading 
in november 
while the nyse remains by far the nations largest exchange 
and the worlds secondlargest behind tokyo its market share has 
eroded and profitability slumped in recent years 
the big board handled only 692 percent of all trades in its 
listed stocks last year an alltime low the exchanges net income 
fell to 629 million last year from 1045 million in 1988 
the nyse still dominates the volume of trades but it has lost 
significant market share to smaller regional exchanges the 
chicagobased midwest stock exchange for example last year 
accounted for 103 percent of the trading in nyse stocks up from 
333 percent in 1979 
industry experts also say erosion has occurred overseas where 
us companies are listed on foreign exchanges 
the london exchange which went electronic four years ago and 
the tokyo market have siphoned the most business in london the 
value of trading of us securities totaled the equivalent of about 
25 billion in may 
another and possibly bigger threat to the nyse is the socalled 
third market of firms that trade stocks off of the exchange 
floor the big board is concerned that its large member firms could 
shift some of their business to offexchange trading 
the third markets share of nyselisted stock trades rose to 74 
percent of overall big board trading through may this year from 31 
percent in the same 1989 period by skirting the nyse floor third 
market firms offer a cheaper and more anonymous way to conduct 
trades 
this electronic alternative to the big board includes 
offexchange firms such as bernard l madoff investment securities 
which can handle trades in 275 of the nyses 1700 listed 
securities the electronic trading system instinet and crossing 
network an afterhours system that matches up trades 
the fully automated national association of securities dealers 
plans to start trading up to 300 overthecounter stocks starting 
at 4 am in september a direct challenge to the london stock 
exchange 
and the american stock exchange said that on monday it would 
outline a joint venture with the chicago board options exchange 
the cincinnati stock exchange and the financial information company 
reuters for trading stocks and options and unregistered securities 
electronically around the world 
how can the 198yearold nyse guarantee its future 
eric k clemons a professor at the university of pennsylvanias 
wharton school said the big board has to make sure institutions 
feel they have no choice that if they want to trade a major us 
stock the only place to trade is new york 
meanwhile nyse competitors and other exchanges welcomed 
phelans proposal to gear up for 24hour trading 
the steps would begin later this year with two brief sessions 
after the markets normal close subsequent phases would involve 
stock auctions held several times a night some form of 
conventional trading overnight and finally 24hour dealing 
andrew yemma a spokesman for the chicago mercantile exchange 
said the nyse moves would help develop an underlying cash market in 
stocks on a 24hour basis that would add liquidity for futures and 
options trading 
it will increase the awareness and attract greater liquidity 
to offhours trading said linda r coleman executive vice 
president of instinet which is owned by reuters holdings plc 
that can only benefit us because it will atrract more trading to 
our orderflow system 
thirdmarket leader bernad madoff said the increased competition 
faced by the nyse is a healthy byproduct of a changing financial 
world 
their concern is not necessarily the concern of the rest of 
the industry madoff said like any business their loss has 
been someone elses gain 
</TEXT>
