us district judge john w bissell should abstain from considering 
allstates grievances because the same case can be litigated 
properly at the state level 
allstate new jerseys largest insurer says the states new law 
violates the companys rights under the fifth and 14th amendments 
because the law unfairly forces the insurance industry to pay 14 
billion to the state highrisk insurance pool 
part of the fifth amendment says the government cannot take 
private property without just compensation and the 14th amendment 
upholds a right to challenge governmental actions 
bissell reserved decision on the matter 
earlier bissell refused a request by the liberty mutual 
insurance group and continental insurance co of new jersey to move 
cases being handled at the state administrative level to the 
federal level 
liberty also has a separate federal case pending that seeks to 
block the insurance law state farm insurance co is seeking the 
same action in state superior court 
the states 15 insurance servicing carriers including allstate 
liberty state farm and continental are named in a state lawsuit 
claiming they overbilled the staterun joint underwriting 
association the case is being handled by an administrative law 
judge 
the insurance law requires the industry to pay the 14 billion 
during the next seven years to help eliminate a 31 billion debt 
amassed by the jua pool for highrisk drivers the jua which costs 
every new jersey motorist 222 per car on their annual policy is 
to be eliminated under the law 
new jerseys car insurance rates are among the nations highest 
