allstate argued friday that under the federal tax injunction act 
the state should not be allowed to collect surcharges and other 
assessments from the company in the form of a tax 
this is a segregated fund which is applied only for the single 
purpose of paying off the jua debt abrams told bissell we 
think that based on case law that neither the assessment nor 
surcharge is a tax we believe it is paying a private debt 
eakeley responded that the surcharge every motorist pays because 
of the jua losses are hardly a private debt 
