uranium division said the company in recent months had tried 
several programs to maintain existing operating levels including 
cost reduction measures and deferment of capital expenditure 
despite these efforts at current gold prices and operating 
costs certain mining areas are now incapable of sustaining mining 
operations at their present levels hewitt said 
he said the curtailment of operations would take place over the 
next nine months and probably result in the loss of 7800 jobs at 
freegold he said reductions at vaal reefs would not necessarily 
eliminate jobs because workers may be assigned to other areas of 
the mine 
operating reductions at freegold would reduce its gold 
production by less than 1 percent while the proposed action at 
vaal reefs likely would improve production hewitt said 
