<TEXT>
british stock market experts said friday they were 
puzzled by the new york stock exchanges plan to begin afterhours 
trading to an effort to recapture trading of us stocks now 
conducted overseas 
the experts said such trading is relatively small in europe and 
it also is not clear that the business will grow much in coming 
years 
but they also said the proposals were too sketchy to determine 
their implications 
one trader however was enthusiastic saying i see this as a 
major plus for internationalization 
big board chairman john j phelan jr on thursday unveiled a 
fivestep plan to phase in a 24hour market by the end of the 
decade to meet increasing competition from overseas 
the steps would begin with two brief sessions after the new york 
markets normal close at 4 pm eastern time 
later stock auctions would be held several times a night 
followed by some form of conventional trading overnight before 
24hour dealing eventually is introduced 
a spokeswoman for londons stock exchange speaking anonymously 
in keeping with british practice said thursday we ourselves 
have no plans to extend trading hours however the exchange 
continues to respond to traders needs 
the london exchange in march moved up its session half an hour 
to between 830 am and 430 pm in respone to demand for 
earlier trading 
the london exchange went electronic four years ago under the 
sweeping big bang deregulation which placed the execution of 
trades on computer screens by contrast the nyse still executes 
trades through the interaction of stock brokers and specialists on 
the exchange floor 
londons specialists are required to continuously make markets 
in stocks during the exchanges official hours but investors are 
allowed to buy and sell shares anytime via computer 
the big boards move probably is in response to nasdaqs plan to 
begin operating during european hours in the third quarter of this 
year said tim williams who runs trading in us stocks for the 
london investment firm county natwest woodmac 
nasdaq or national association of securities dealers automated 
quotations is an american screenbased overthecounter market 
its a bit difficult to understand really what they the big 
board are going to accomplish by it williams said friday the 
fact of the matter is most of the business here is reasonably 
small whether it can be developed is debatable 
the london exchange said the value of trading in us stocks in 
london came to the equivalent of about 26 billion in may 
