going to be because theyre very sketchy about what they want to 
do williams said about phelans plan 
investors are unlikely to be willing to wait around for the 
appointed time or agree to an auction he said 
he also said he didnt think investors would be willing to risk 
leaving an overnight order with a broker because a market 
development could occur while the investor is asleep 
he noted that london brokers place overnight orders in tokyo 
but were used to it he said 
im no sure there is going to be global trading he added 
but the enthusiastic london trader who didnt want to be 
identified said we welcome any kind of competition in europe 
