<TEXT>
bond prices tumbled friday on economic reports 
that led traders to conclude the federal reserve did not plan to 
lower shortterm interest rates soon 
in its sharpest oneday drop since midapril the treasurys 
benchmark 30year bond tumbled 1316 point or 813 per 1000 in 
face amount 
its yield which rises when prices fall climbed to 842 percent 
from late wednesdays 834 percent which was the lowest for the 
longterm bond since late january 
economists said they were surprised at the sharp drop which 
came despite news on inflation and the federal trade deficit that 
normally would give bond prices a boost 
they attributed the bulk of the decline to a fed report that 
industrial production rebounded an unexpectedly strong 06 percent 
last month after holding steady in april the market had expected a 
03 percent rise 
some analysts said the market should have dismissed the gain in 
industrial production because it was caused mainly by a buildup in 
inventories by the big three automakers concerned about a possible 
strike 
signs of a strong economy tend to weaken bonds because of 
concerns that inflation will rise and erode the value of such 
longterm fixedincome investments 
the labor department reported retail prices rose a modest 02 
percent in may bringing the rise in the consumer price index for 
the first five months of the year to 58 percent that news should 
have been favorable for credit markets 
in addition the commerce department said the us trade deficit 
shrank to 694 billion in april the second lowest level in the 
last 6 years another positive sign 
ray stone managing director of stone amp mccarthy research 
associates inc said the market declined following a financial 
wire report citing unnamed fed officials who reinforced a view they 
werent close to lowering interest rates 
traders believed the economy was not weak enough nor inflation 
calm enough to trigger an easier monetary policy falling interest 
rates boost the value of existing bonds because their rates of 
return are higher and therefore more valuable 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments fell 316 point to 932 point intermediate maturities 
