<TEXT>
donald trump missed a payment due friday on junk 
bonds used to finance one of his atlantic city resorts the 
harshest signal yet of the troubles plaguing his tottering real 
estate empire 
trump has a 10day grace period to make the payment of an 
estimated 31 million in interest and principal on bonds used to 
finance his trump castle hotelcasino 
but the failure to meet fridays deadline nevertheless brought 
him a step closer to default which theoretically could force a 
bankruptcy filing to defend the flamboyant developer from 
collateralseeking creditors 
what this tells us is he has not been able to reach a deal 
with his banks michael mulvaney a bond analyst with moodys 
investors services inc said of the missed payment he has the 
grace period to work it out if he doesnt work it out then youve 
got the possibility of default 
separately moodys a major wall street credit rating firm on 
friday lowered its ratings for bonds used to finance the trump taj 
mahal and trump plaza hotelcasinos moodys said the missed 
payment for trump castle showed the potential for weakened finances 
at the other two resorts 
a statement issued by the trump organization announcing the 
missed payment said negotiations were continuing with lenders to 
get more money and restructure loans 
trump and his main bankers tentatively had agreed a week ago to 
a bailout that would have provided him another 60 million in loans 
and a temporary suspension of payments in exchange the banks 
would have gotten equity in some of his properties 
if the deal had been finalized he would have had the cash to 
make fridays bond payment 
but other banks involved in the deal reportedly balked at the 
plan first fidelity bancorp of newark nj and midlantic banks 
inc of edison nj reportedly were the main holdouts midlantic 
would not comment on the situation friday 
late friday first fidelity announced it would resign as trustee 
for the bondholders once a successor is found the bank said it 
wanted to avoid the appearance of a conflict of interest in its 
role as both a bank lender and overseer of bondholders interest as 
trustee 
spokesmen for his four major bank lenders citicorp chase 
manhattan bankers trust and manufacturers hanover either would 
not comment or did not return telephone calls 
trump has been beset by a slumping real estate market in new 
york and disappointing results from his three atlantic city 
casinos and the trump shuttle airline 
his real estate holdings which also include new yorks plaza 
hotel and trump tower were built largely with funds borrowed with 
junk bonds and bank loans trump owes banks an estimated 2 billion 
and bondholders another 1 billion 
the ongoing negotiations have raised speculation that bankers 
want more authority over operation of his properties possibly even 
naming new managers and leaving trump only as a figurehead 
the negotiations also have caught the eye of the new jersey 
casino control commission 
its always a matter of concern when any casino is in 
difficulty said tom flynn a commission spokesman also the new 
jersey division of gaming enforcement has been auditing trumps 
properties for more than a month the dge an arm of the state 
attorney generals office has characterized the audit as routine 
fridays payment was due on two bonds issued to finance the 
trump castle one paying 1375 percent due in 1997 and one paying 7 
percent due in 1999 
trump who bought back many of his bonds at a discount on the 
open market owes about 12 million in interest and 10 million in 
principal on the 1375 percent bonds and about 9 million on the 7 
percent bonds according to sheila oconnell a bond analyst with 
duff amp phelps a chicago investment firm 
the total amount trump would owe if he had not bought back any 
bonds is 426 million 
in the first three months of 1990 trump castle lost 84 
million the largest loss among the 12 casinos in atlantic city 
trump castle recorded improved gross gaming revenues for the 
first three months of the year but failed to maintain those gains 
after the taj mahal opened april 2 
trump castles win in may fell 173 percent from a year 
earlier to 179 million 
the win is the amount of money a casino wins at gaming 
tables and slot machines and does not account for operating 
expenses depreciation debt service taxes and other charges 
for may the taj mahal broke its own citywide record for win 
with 365 million or 118 million a day trump plaza helped by 
a 10 million windfall from an unlucky japanese high roller at the 
baccarat table posted a win of 313 million up 23 percent from 
may 1989 
</TEXT>
